---
description: Enforce shadcn-vue-first UI composition and MCP-docs-first behavior
alwaysApply: true
---

# shadcn-vue UI Source of Truth

- Base UI primitives MUST come from shadcn-vue patterns/components.
- MUST NOT rebuild base controls manually (`button`, `input`, `dialog`, `card`, `tabs`, `select`, `table`).
- Before UI generation or edits, MUST consult shadcn-vue MCP documentation first, then implement.
- MUST NEVER assume props/events/slots for shadcn-based components without checking docs.

# Composition Guidance

- Use `components/atoms` as thin wrappers around shadcn-vue building blocks.
- Build `molecules` and `organisms` by composing atoms, not by duplicating primitive behavior.
- Keep styling consistent with the existing shadcn-vue approach and utility classes.
- Avoid overriding shadcn core behavior unless required by product requirements.

# Forbidden

- Creating ad-hoc replacements for standard shadcn primitives.
- Introducing custom APIs for atoms that conflict with underlying shadcn behavior.
- Mixing business logic into shadcn atom wrappers.

# Compliance Gate

- If shadcn MCP docs are not checked first, pause implementation and fetch docs before coding.
- If requested UI conflicts with official shadcn patterns, provide a compliant shadcn-based alternative.
